<div id=3D"text-text-142bce8299" class=3D"cmp-text   is-rtf">
    <ul>
<li>Password</li>
<li>123456</li>
<li>Qwerty</li>
<li>Your child's name</li>
<li>The same password for everything.</li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: -0.3px;">These passwords are easy to crac=
k. If you use one password for multiple logins, if one of your logins is co=
mpromised, a hacker has access to other logins too. Or, for example, if you=
 use your child name and your device has been compromised by a <a href=3D"h=
ttps://us.norton.com/blog/malware/what-is-a-computer-virus">virus</a> or <a=
 href=3D"https://us.norton.com/blog/emerging-threats/malware">malware</a>, =
a hacker will have access to that information and thus easily replicate you=
r other passwords.</span></p>

